= DESCRIPTION =

    "WWW::Rafb" provides object interface for pasting any text file/source file
    into the the rafb site with the needed information.

= INSTALL =

    WWW::Rafb uses the following modules:

	URI::Escape - to escape the args before sending.
	LWP::UserAgent 	- to create the post of the paste.
 
    Before installing make sure you have this modules: URI::Escape , LWP::UserAgent.
    If you dont: enter cpan command shell (`cpan`) and run install LWP::Simple
							   install URI::Escape (if isnt installed)
    After that run this commands:
	
            perl Makefile.PL
            make
            make test
            make install

    then perldoc WWW::Rafb.

